 is available On-Prem or in the Cloud. With Amadeo, you get more than voice and video, you get a complete and secure enterprise communications suite: Presence IM Persistent Chat Audio Video Desktop/App Sharing Whiteboarding File Sharing Document Sharing PBX Functions PSTN/SIP Trunking Federation Escalation De-escalation Modalities 323 Sessions Room Based HD Video Conferencing Sessions 3rd Party Meeting Integration Conference Session Recording Sweeping® TabShare /SmartShare Parallel Edits Scheduled Meetings Push Notification Can Amadeo replace my old PBX or IP-PBX? Yes, Amadeo has built in PBX capabilities. Amadeo PBX can be used to replace a PBX or IP-PBX. Will Amadeo work with my existing SIP PBX? Yes, Amadeo can work with your existing SIP PBX. Can Amadeo replace current online meeting solutions? Yes, Amadeo has online meeting and conferencing capabilities. Is audio conferencing included in Amadeo? Yes. Is a multi-tenant architecture supported in Amadeo? Yes, please contact an authorized Amadeo reseller. Can I connect my current PSTN lines to Amadeo Cloud services? Yes. Can I sign into multiple devices at once? Amadeo has Sweeping™, which allows an active session to be transferred from one device to another. How can I purchase Amadeo? Amadeo Cloud - Self Service or Authorized Reseller Amadeo On-Prem - Authorized Reseller Amadeo Cloud Premium - Authorized Reseller Do I need an Amadeo Cloud License per device? No. Amadeo licensing is user based. This allows your users to be able to install Amadeo on multiple devices. How can I get started with Amadeo? If your company is using Amadeo, all you need is: A valid account Any supported device with the Amadeo client installed. Do I have to pay to download the Amadeo client? No, the Amadeo client is available for free for Windows/Mac OS/Linux and iOS/Android. Are telephony voice services included in the Software Licensing Price? No, IP telephony services are charged separately. Where do I get the Amadeo client? Links to the clients can be found via theAmadeo Cloud Download page Mobile clients are available on the Apple™ AppStore and Google Play. How do I install the Amadeo client? Please use the following link to download the Amadeo Client Installation Guide. We need to add a user to our existing account. How will that be billed? Every account is assigned with billing terms. When adding users, your account will be charged with the prorated license amount to the billing date. On the renewal date your account will be charged for all the existing users. How do you bill telephony voice services? Voice services and related fees are charged against the account&apos;s prepaid balance or line of credit. If the account is out of credit, voice services will be suspended. The Amadeo system will generate a detailed invoice according to subscription plan billing terms. Are services renewed automatically? Yes, as long as the account has enough balance or credit. How do I cancel my Amadeo Cloud subscription? On the Amadeo Cloud Portal you are able to cancel the renewal of your subscription. Services will continue as active until the end of the billing period. We do not offer refunds. We can&apos;t pay by credit card, can you invoice my company? Yes, in addition to credit card, we accept wire transfers and check as payment methods. How can I get Amadeo Support? Support is available through the Amadeo Customer Portal and by phone/IM/video for customers with a Premium Support License. We do provide some -How To- guides for end users, available in the Amadeo support section What kind of support is included in the Amadeo Cloud license price? Amadeo basic support includes: Access to the Amadeo Support Portal Ability to Submit and Track Support Tickets Free Amadeo client upgrades and updates (bug-fixes, enhancements) Product documentation Latest Tweet Damaka Introduces Amadeo Cloud™ #UCC Service for Small to Medium Sized Businesses http://t.co/i13jImxJCx #SMB #mobilebiz #VoIP #enterprise3:42 PM Jul 31st Co